Definitions
User
means any entity, organization, corporation or living natural person that uses the Services and/or interacts with Resolution Games in any way.
Data Processor
means anyone who Processes Personal Data on behalf of a Data Controller.
Data Controller
means a legal entity, who alone or jointly with others, determines the purposes and means of the Processing of Personal Data.
Data Protection Legislation
means the applicable data protection legislation such as Regulation (EU) 2016/679 (General Data Protection Regulation; the “GDPR”) and any other applicable data protection legislation.
EU/EEA
means the European Union/European Economic Area.
Personal Data
means any information that, directly or indirectly, can identify a natural person.
Processing
means any operation or set of operations performed with regard to Personal Data, whether or not performed by automated means, such as collection, recording, organisation, storage, adaptation, alteration, retrieval, gathering, use, combination, blocking, erasure or destruction.
Recipient
means a natural or legal person, public authority or another body, to whom Personal Data may be disclosed to by Resolution Games.
Services
means any of Resolution Games’ services and/or games as well as communications provided on Resolution Games’ websites and other electronic channels.
General
This Privacy Policy describes how Resolution Games AB as a Data Controller Processes User’s Personal Data on a general level. Specific information about further Processing can be found in separate agreements, websites or other documents related to Resolution Games.
Resolution Games may need to Process Personal Data in order to provide the Services to the Users, fulfil legal obligation or for the performance of agreements. If a User chooses not to provide or submit Personal Data in the Services, it may prevent Resolution Games to fulfilling the abovementioned obligations. In some cases, Users may not be able to use and access the Services, such as multiplayer features of the games provided by Resolution Games.
Resolution Games ensures the confidentiality of Personal Data and has implemented appropriate technical and organizational measures to safeguard Personal Data from unathorized access, unlawful disclosure, accidental loss, modification, destruction or any other unlawful Processing.
Resolution Games may use approved Data Processors for Processing Personal Data. Resolution Games ensures that Data Processors Process Personal Data under documented instructions of Resolution Games which are in accordance with adequate and required security measures in accordance with Data Protection Legislation.
Personal Data of children
The Services are not directed or intended for children and Resolution Games does not knowingly collect Personal Data from children under 18 years old in the Services. Resolution Games prohibits submission of Personal Data by children, unless sent under the supervision of their parent or guardian. It is important to safeguard the privacy of children and Resolution Games encourages parents to regularly monitor their children’s use of online activities. Resolution Games will promptly delete Personal Data submitted by children unless legally obligated to retain such data.
Resolution Games requests that any parents to children under the age of 18 that may have submitted Personal Data to make contact at
privacy@resolutiongames.com
.
Security
Resolution Games has taken reasonable steps to ensure that Personal Data it collects is secure and reasonable measures are put in place to protect the confidentiality, security, and integrity of the Personal Data collected from our Users. Personal Data is stored in secure operating environments that are not available to the public and that are only accessible to authorized employees and contractors. Resolution Games also has security measures in place to protect the loss, misuse, and alteration of the information under our control.
Please note that Resolution Games may provide links to other games and websites that are operated and hosted by third parties who may have their own privacy policies. The Processing of Personal Data by third parties in other games and websites are governed by their own privacy policies, which may be substantially different from this Privacy Policy. Visitors to other games and websites are encouraged to review the privacy policies and information collection practices of those websites.
Any improper collection or misuse of User Created Content or information provided in the Game is a violation of the Terms of Use and should be reported to Resolution Games at
privacy@resolutiongames.com
.
Collection of Personal Data and categories of Data Subjects
Resolution Games primarily collects from and Processes Personal Data of Users of the Services, such as players of the games provided by Resolution Games. Personal Data may be collected from Users directly, by User’s submission of Personal Data and/or automatically from the use of the Services. Resolution Games may also save electronic communications or otherwise document Resolution Games’ interaction and communication with Users in various electronic channels. Resolution Games also collects non-personal identifiable information, such as anonymous gameplay data and statistical information, derived from the Services, in order to improve the Services.
Resolution Games also collects and Processes Personal Data from prospect customers, agents, legal representatives, corporate representatives, signatories, shareholders, contact persons, board members, job applicants and visitors of Resolution Games’ offices. For job applicants, please also see the privacy policy available on Resolution Games’ job applications website.
Resolution Games may also collect Personal Data from other sources, such as third party sites or platforms, newspapers, blogs, instant messaging services in order to improve and provide the Services as well as a more personalized experience. Resolution Games will in some cases ask for email addresses for sales and marketing purposes.
Categories of Personal Data
The main categories of Personal Data Processed by Resolution Games include:
Identification and contact information
such as name, personal identification code/number, internet procotol (IP) address, online nickname, date of birth, address, telephone number, email address and country of residence.
Communication information
such as complaints/support matters in voice/written form, images and/or audio recordings, emails, messages and other communications such as socia media.
Electronic interaction information
such as the type of browser that is used, the type of operating system that is used, the IP address or other unique identifier such as a device identifier of any computer(s) or device(s) that are used to access electronic channels.
Legal basis and purpose of Processing
Performance of agreements
Resolution Games Processes Personal Data to fulfil obligations in agreements with external parties. This Processing relates to the execution, documentation and administration of agreements entered into by Resolution Games. Examples of purposes for Processing are to verify transactions with business partners, to perform play- and beta tests and to provide the games as part of the Services.
Legal obligations
Resolution Games Processes Personal Data in order to fulfil legal obligations imposed by regulators. Examples of purposes for Processing are to identify Users in order to make sure that Resolution Games does not collect Personal Data from children aswell as to comply to book keeping obligations.
Consent
Resolution Games Processes Personal Data in some cases when Users have provided their consent to it and the provided consent can always be withdrawn. An example of purpose for Processing is when subscribing to Resolution Games’ newsletter.
Legitimate interest
Resolution Games Processes Personal Data based on Resolution Games’ legitimate interest. Resolution Games have concluded this Processing necessary for the interest pursued by Resolution Games, which outweighs the User’s interest of protection of the Personal Data. Examples of purposes for Processing are to improve the Services, to provide personalized offers and direct marketing and to organize competitions and campaigns.
Cookies
Cookies are used by Resolution Games for different purposes when visiting Resolution Games’ websites. All cookies used are listed in the
Cookie Declaration
available on Resolution Games’ website.
Links to third-party platforms
Resolution Games may provide links to third-party platforms where Users can purchase games developed by Resolution Games. These links are known as affiliate links, and Resolution Games may be compensated when Users use these links to make a purchase. When you click on an affiliate link and make a purchase, the third-party platform may use cookies or other tracking technologies to track your purchases and ensure that Resolution Games receives credit for the referral. These third-party platforms have their own privacy policies, and you are encouraged to review them to understand how Personal Data may be collected and used.
Recipients of Personal Data
Based on the legal bases and the purposes for Processing by Resolution Games, Resolution Games may share User’s Personal Data with Recipients to Process Personal Data as a Data Processor. Resolution Games will only share necessary Personal Data for the purposes of the disclosure and never for the Recipients own purposes. Further, Resolution Games will only share Personal Data if the Recipients have ensured an adequate level of protection of the Personal Data in accordance with Data Protection Legislation. Resolution Games may also share anonymous or aggregated information, or other data that is not considered Personal Data with third parties, for example personas on leaderboards or to show trends about the use of Resolution Games’ Services.
Third party agents/contractors/developers
.
